<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="387" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,319,885]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,379,319,344]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Material examined</emphasis>
. No specimen was examined by us, but the 
<typeStatus box="[886,984,319,344]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">holotype</typeStatus>
was examined and images provided by Robin Ngiam. The comparison of the photographs (
<figureCitation box="[745,823,356,381]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1935,1957]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,940,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,940,1914]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Holotype of Eucriotettix ridleyi body in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views; (C) labels. Image by Robin Ngiam." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/580498/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
A–C) with original description based on the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,356,381]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">holotype</typeStatus>
only (
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther" box="[215,379,391,416]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" refString="Gunther, K. (1938) Revision der Acrydiinae (Orth.) II. Scelimenae spuriae. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 99, 117 - 148, 161 - 230." type="journal article" year="1938">Günther, 1938</bibRefCitation>
) allow us to add some important characters in the diagnosis of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="387" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,319,885]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,458,428,453]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
. Vertex 1.4 times narrower than one eye seen from above. Antennal socket situated between the lower margins of eyes. External lateral carina of pronotum distinctly raised, infrascapular area broadened (
<figureCitation box="[288,360,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1935,1957]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,940,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,940,1914]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Holotype of Eucriotettix ridleyi body in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views; (C) labels. Image by Robin Ngiam." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/580498/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
А). Lower side of the lateral lobes of pronotum deeply excised behind triangularly pointed projection (
<figureCitation box="[281,349,535,560]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1935,1957]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,940,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,940,1914]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Holotype of Eucriotettix ridleyi body in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views; (C) labels. Image by Robin Ngiam." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/580498/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
B). Hind femur 3.2 times as long as wide. 
<taxonomicName box="[832,1045,536,560]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ridleyi">
<emphasis box="[832,1045,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Eucriotettix ridleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock, 1912" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[1194,1312,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">E. grandis</emphasis>
(Hancock, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock 1915" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1915" box="[271,586,572,597]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dohertyi">
<emphasis box="[271,395,572,596]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">E. dohertyi</emphasis>
(Hancock 1915)
</taxonomicName>
, sharing the absence of a long spine on lower side of the pronotal lobes and the posterior pronotal process reaching two thirds of hind tibiae. 
<taxonomicName box="[889,995,608,632]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ridleyi">
<emphasis box="[889,906,609,632]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[922,995,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">ridleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1264,608,632]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[1147,1264,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">E. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the external lateral carina of pronotum (in 
<taxonomicName box="[488,605,644,668]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[488,605,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">E. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
these carina almost straight) while the shape of lower side of pronotum is the same in both species and differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[637,756,680,704]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doherty">
<emphasis box="[637,756,680,704]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">E. doherty</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in latter species the lower side almost quadrate, obliquely truncate posteriorly and gently notched). The differences of 
<taxonomicName box="[834,940,716,740]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eucriotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ridleyi">
<emphasis box="[834,851,717,740]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[867,940,716,740]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">ridleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Singaporean congeners are given in a key above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
